category: Python
requires: alternatives python39
sdesc: "Seamless operability between C++11 and Python"
ldesc: "pybind11 is a lightweight header library that exposes C++ types in Python and vice versa, mainly to create Python bindings of existing C++ code. Its goals and syntax are similar to the excellent Boost.Python library by David Abrahams: to minimize boilerplate code in traditional extension modules by inferring type information using compile-time introspection."
external-source: python-pybind11

